{"node_id": "700a67e70efb54f9a79ff4ae7da314e2", "title": "Derivatives of sin(x) and cos(x)", "description": "Find the derivatives of functions that contain sin(x) or cos(x). For example, differentiate f(x)=2x+3sin(x).", "topic_path": ["Khan Academy (English - US curriculum)", "Math", "AP®︎ Calculus AB", "Differentiation: definition and basic derivative rules", "Derivatives of cos(x), sin(x), 𝑒ˣ, and ln(x)", "Derivatives of sin(x) and cos(x)"], "assessment_items": [{"item_id": "72b5decac268599c83e2ad6b212f6c20", "question_content": "Let $f(x)=2x-3\\sin(x)$.\n\n$f'(x)=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression for $f(x)$ includes $\\sin(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\sin(x)$ is $\\cos(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]=\\cos(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\nf'(x)&=\\dfrac{d}{dx}[2x-3\\sin(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x)-3\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\cdot1-3\\cdot\\cos(x)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=2-3\\cos(x)\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$f'(x)=2-3\\cos(x)$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["2-3\\cos\\left(x\\right)"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 0, "simplify": false, "value": "2-3\\cos\\left(x\\right)"}]}}}, {"item_id": "84ac32e971c45f828a8293fd3db7c498", "question_content": "Let $g(x)=5x^2+4\\sin(x)$.\n\n$g'(x)=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression for $g(x)$ includes $\\sin(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\sin(x)$ is $\\cos(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]=\\cos(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\ng'(x)&=\\dfrac{d}{dx}[5x^2+4\\sin(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=5\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)+4\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=5\\cdot2x+4\\cdot\\cos(x)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=10x+4\\cos(x)\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$g'(x)=10x+4\\cos(x)$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["10x+4\\cos\\left(x\\right)"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 0, "simplify": false, "value": "10x+4\\cos\\left(x\\right)"}]}}}, {"item_id": "52bde6f3f7c85cedb81ee091c1f4fb5f", "question_content": "Let $h(x)=-6\\sin(x)-3x$.\n\n$h'(x)=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression for $h(x)$ includes $\\sin(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\sin(x)$ is $\\cos(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]=\\cos(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\nh'(x)&=\\dfrac{d}{dx}[-6\\sin(x)-3x]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-6\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]-3\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-6\\cdot\\cos(x)-3\\cdot1\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-6\\cos(x)-3\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$h'(x)=-6\\cos(x)-3$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["-6\\cos\\left(x\\right)-3"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 0, "simplify": false, "value": "-6\\cos\\left(x\\right)-3"}]}}}, {"item_id": "529a3101ef865b8c9fb63c28facfa8b4", "question_content": "Let $f(x)=7\\sin(x)-2x^3$.\n\n$f'(x)=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression for $f(x)$ includes $\\sin(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\sin(x)$ is $\\cos(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]=\\cos(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\nf'(x)&=\\dfrac{d}{dx}[7\\sin(x)-2x^3]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=7\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]-2\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=7\\cdot\\cos(x)-2\\cdot3x^2\n\\\\\\\\\n&=7\\cos(x)-6x^2\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$f'(x)=7\\cos(x)-6x^2$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["7\\cos\\left(x\\right)-6x^{2}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": "0", "simplify": false, "value": "7\\cos\\left(x\\right)-6x^{2}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "7a4982f311a951dd8f0c6078fd75fdb9", "question_content": "$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[5\\sin(x)+x^2]=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression to differentiate includes $\\sin(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\sin(x)$ is $\\cos(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]=\\cos(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{d}{dx}[5\\sin(x)+x^2]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=5\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]+\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=5\\cos(x)+2x\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[5\\sin(x)+x^2]=5\\cos(x)+2x$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["5\\cos\\left(x\\right)+2x"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 0, "simplify": false, "value": "5\\cos\\left(x\\right)+2x"}]}}}, {"item_id": "75a677cc820f5bf884e32873a9bd75d2", "question_content": "$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[-4\\sin(x)+9x]=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression to differentiate includes $\\sin(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\sin(x)$ is $\\cos(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]=\\cos(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{d}{dx}[-4\\sin(x)+9x]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-4\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]+9\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-4\\cdot \\cos(x)+9\\cdot 1\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-4\\cos(x)+9\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[-4\\sin(x)+9x]=-4\\cos(x)+9$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["-4\\cos\\left(x\\right)+9"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 0, "simplify": false, "value": "-4\\cos\\left(x\\right)+9"}]}}}, {"item_id": "58e557b1702f51bba770222d9432f972", "question_content": "$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[8\\sin(x)-x]=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression to differentiate includes $\\sin(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\sin(x)$ is $\\cos(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]=\\cos(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{d}{dx}[8\\sin(x)-x]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=8\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]-\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=8\\cdot \\cos(x)-1\n\\\\\\\\\n&=8\\cos(x)-1\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[8\\sin(x)-x]=8\\cos(x)-1$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["8\\cos\\left(x\\right)-1"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 0, "simplify": false, "value": "8\\cos\\left(x\\right)-1"}]}}}, {"item_id": "dbaf35aeab315a609da2977986568553", "question_content": "$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[-4x^3-\\sin(x)]=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression to differentiate includes $\\sin(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\sin(x)$ is $\\cos(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]=\\cos(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{d}{dx}[-4x^3-\\sin(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-4\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)-\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-4\\cdot 3x^2-\\cos(x)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-12x^2-\\cos(x)\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[-4x^3-\\sin(x)]=-12x^2-\\cos(x)$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["-12x^{2}-\\cos\\left(x\\right)"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": "0", "simplify": false, "value": "-12x^{2}-\\cos\\left(x\\right)"}]}}}, {"item_id": "3df5854104e25f889c6ccab63253690c", "question_content": "Let $g(x)=-2\\cos(x)+3x^3$.\n\n$g'(x)=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression for $g(x)$ includes $\\cos(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\cos(x)$ is $-\\sin(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]=-\\sin(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\ng'(x)&=\\dfrac{d}{dx}[-2\\cos(x)+3x^3]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-2\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]+3\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-2(-\\sin(x))+3\\cdot3x^2\n\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\sin(x)+9x^2\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$g'(x)=2\\sin(x)+9x^2$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["2\\sin\\left(x\\right)+9x^2"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 0, "simplify": false, "value": "2\\sin\\left(x\\right)+9x^2"}]}}}, {"item_id": "218d2aa877ae5002aea28d4b130797ae", "question_content": "Let $h(x)=9\\cos(x)-7x^2$.\n\n$h'(x)=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression for $h(x)$ includes $\\cos(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\cos(x)$ is $-\\sin(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]=-\\sin(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\nh'(x)&=\\dfrac{d}{dx}[9\\cos(x)-7x^2]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=9\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]-7\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=9(-\\sin(x))-7\\cdot2x\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-9\\sin(x)-14x\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$h'(x)=-9\\sin(x)-14x$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["-9\\sin\\left(x\\right)-14x"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 0, "simplify": false, "value": "-9\\sin\\left(x\\right)-14x"}]}}}, {"item_id": "75dcd1cd8aca5be6b9b4da9351fc6a55", "question_content": "Let $f(x)=5x^3-6\\cos(x)$.\n\n$f'(x)=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression for $f(x)$ includes $\\cos(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\cos(x)$ is $-\\sin(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]=-\\sin(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\nf'(x)&=\\dfrac{d}{dx}[5x^3-6\\cos(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=5\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)-6\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=5\\cdot(3x^2)-6(-\\sin(x))\n\\\\\\\\\n&=15x^2+6\\sin(x)\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$f'(x)=15x^2+6\\sin(x)$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["15x^2+6\\sin\\left(x\\right)"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 0, "simplify": false, "value": "15x^2+6\\sin\\left(x\\right)"}]}}}, {"item_id": "bcd6187b60e354aba74999aac9693704", "question_content": "Let $g(x)=-8x-\\cos(x)$.\n\n$g'(x)=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression for $g(x)$ includes $\\cos(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\cos(x)$ is $-\\sin(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]=-\\sin(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\ng'(x)&=\\dfrac{d}{dx}[-8x-\\cos(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-8\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x)-\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-8\\cdot (1)-(-\\sin(x))\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-8+\\sin(x)\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$g'(x)=-8+\\sin(x)$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["-8+\\sin\\left(x\\right)"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 0, "simplify": false, "value": "-8+\\sin\\left(x\\right)"}]}}}, {"item_id": "56770c74953c53d2a7a9e2fc27054a19", "question_content": "$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)-7x]=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression to differentiate includes $\\cos(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\cos(x)$ is $-\\sin(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]=-\\sin(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)-7x]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]-7\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-\\sin(x)-7\\cdot1\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-\\sin(x)-7\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)-7x]=-\\sin(x)-7$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["-\\sin\\left(x\\right)-7"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 0, "simplify": false, "value": "-\\sin\\left(x\\right)-7"}]}}}, {"item_id": "11f7b2238fc25ac1a0cd79ee40f0e9ad", "question_content": "$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[3\\cos(x)+4x^2]=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression to differentiate includes $\\cos(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\cos(x)$ is $-\\sin(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]=-\\sin(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{d}{dx}[3\\cos(x)+4x^2]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=3\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]+4\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=3(-\\sin(x))+4\\cdot2x\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-3\\sin(x)+8x\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[3\\cos(x)+4x^2]=-3\\sin(x)+8x$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["-3\\sin\\left(x\\right)+8x"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 0, "simplify": false, "value": "-3\\sin\\left(x\\right)+8x"}]}}}, {"item_id": "42a351253d68550bb1dcd2eed426afab", "question_content": "$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[-5x^2-4\\cos(x)]=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression to differentiate includes $\\cos(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\cos(x)$ is $-\\sin(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]=-\\sin(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{d}{dx}[-5x^2-4\\cos(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-5\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)-4\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-5\\cdot 2x-4(-\\sin(x))\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-10x+4\\sin(x)\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[-5x^2-4\\cos(x)]=-10x+4\\sin(x)$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["-10x+4\\sin\\left(x\\right)"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 0, "simplify": false, "value": "-10x+4\\sin\\left(x\\right)"}]}}}, {"item_id": "d3315739c55f52cd85c2182367100e3c", "question_content": "$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[x^3-\\cos(x)]=$ [[☃ expression 1]]", "hints": ["The expression to differentiate includes $\\cos(x)$.\n\nRemember that the derivative of $\\cos(x)$ is $-\\sin(x)$.\n\nPut another way, $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]=-\\sin(x)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{d}{dx}[x^3-\\cos(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)-\\dfrac{d}{dx}[\\cos(x)]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=3x^2-(-\\sin(x))\n\\\\\\\\\n&=3x^2+\\sin(x)\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{d}{dx}[x^3-\\cos(x)]=3x^2+\\sin(x)$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["3x^{2}+\\sin\\left(x\\right)"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": "0", "simplify": false, "value": "3x^{2}+\\sin\\left(x\\right)"}]}}}], "mastery_model": {"type": "m_of_n", "m": 3, "n": 4}, "randomize": true}